x4freetext: A detailed
discussion of the experimental uncertainties.

uncertainties which have to be taken into account was
already given in REL-REF.
The uncertainties cover those of the primary
proton energies and the energy straggling in the stack.
By F.C.

x4freetext: Strontium was Irradiated As Sr-F/2 in Form of
Circular Cristals with 15 mm Diameter with a Typical
Weight of 900 Milligramm.
For Proton Energies Above 500 MeV Each Three Sr Target
Were Put Together in Order to Minimize Recoil Losses
And Cross Contaminations by Analyzing Only the Targets
In the Middle of a Set of Three.
Only One Sr-F/2 Target was Irradiated For Lower Proton
Energies in Order to Provide a Large Number of Energy
Points in Spite of the Proton Stopping  Becoming  Large
At these Energies.
